04/08/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The police announced on Tuesday (August 3rd) they have arrested two people for an attack on Serbian journalist Teofil Pancic. 
The two suspects, both in their 20s, were detained in Belgrade. 
They will appear before an investigative judge for interrogation. 
Teofil Pancic was attacked by two assailants wielding metal bars aboard a public bus on July 24th in Belgrade. 
He suffered head and arm injuries. 
Pancic, a columnist for Vreme weekly, is a fierce critic of Serbian nationalism. 
(RTS, Tanjug, B92, AP - 03/08/10)
